# Building 1000 ICP-Qualified Companies in One Month

If I was given this internship, I would treat this as building a repeatable research engine rather than manually searching company names.

The objective would not be collecting 1000 companies, but creating a pipeline that discovers thousands of companies and filters them down to 1000 true Federer ICP companies.

My approach would combine:

* Structured databases
* Automated data extraction
* AI-assisted enrichment
* Human quality checks

---

# 1. Creating the Initial Company Universe

## Target:

Build an initial universe of around 8,000–10,000 companies.

Since the final requirement is 1000 qualified companies, starting with only 1000 companies would create quality problems.

I would collect companies from multiple sources:

---

## Government & Industry Databases

### MCA Company Data

Purpose:

Identify registered manufacturing companies.

Data collected:

* Company name
* Age
* Directors
* Location
* Industry classification

Why useful:

Federer companies are usually founder/operator-led businesses, so MCA helps identify leadership and ownership signals.

---

### MSME / Udyam / Industrial Directories

Purpose:

Find hidden mid-market manufacturers.

Useful for:

* Precision engineering companies
* Industrial manufacturers
* Specialty manufacturers

Many Federer companies have low marketing visibility but appear in industrial records.

---

### Export & Industry Bodies

Sources:

* EEPC India
* Pharmexcil
* ACMA
* SIDM
* Medical device associations
* Electronics manufacturing associations

Why useful:

Export-focused companies usually have:

* Better systems
* Certifications
* Higher operational maturity

These directly map to C3 and C7 scoring.

---

### Trade Shows & Exhibitor Lists

Examples:

* Aero India
* IMTEX
* Medical Fair India
* Automation Expo
* Pharma exhibitions

Reason:

Companies investing in exhibitions usually have:

* Growth intent
* New products
* Expansion plans

Useful signals for C5 and C6.

---

